Class ProcessLauncher

java.lang.Object
  com.orchestranetworks.workflow.ProcessLauncher
public final class ProcessLauncher

Prepares and launches a process instance. A ProcessLauncher is created using WorkflowEngine.getProcessLauncher(PublishedProcessKey)

launchProcess

public ProcessInstanceKey launchProcess()
                                 throws OperationException
Starts a new process instance as it has been specified by this launcher. It can be called several times. It will create each time a new process instance.

Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - if the specified name is not declared in the process definition's data context, or the corresponding variable is not declared as being an input parameter.
OperationException
